<L>__{interior a restaurant restroom day >}
<A>__{leonard, in beige suit and blue shirt flushes the urinal, then moves to the sink and starts washing his hands. he notices a message written on the back of his hand. "remember sammy jankis" he stares at the message for a second, thoughtful, then tries to scrub the writing off his skin. to his surprise, it is indelible. leonard looks at it, quizzical, then notices some markings on his wrist, pulling his sleeve back to get a better look. he can read the start of a message: "the facts:" leonard is about to roll his sleeve up further when the restroom door opens and a man enters. leonard dries his hands, then exits the rest room.}
